New Records: Glenn Maxwell's 40-ball century is the fastest ever at a 50-over World Cup, beating Aiden Markram's record set just 18 days prior.
Bas de Leede conceded 115 runs in his 10 overs, the most by a bowler in a men's ODI.
Key Match Events: Glenn Maxwell produced a blistering 106 off 44 balls.
Australia racked up 8-399 after electing to bat.
The Netherlands were bowled out for 90 in 21 overs, resulting in the biggest defeat in the tournament's history.
Logan van Beek took 4 wickets for 74 runs.
Adam Zampa claimed three wickets for eight runs.
Pre-Game Insights: Mitchell Marsh retained his place as Warner's opening partner due to Travis Head's recovery from a fractured hand.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Australia plundered 131 runs in the final 10 overs.
The Netherlands began with spin from both ends.
David Warner hit four consecutive fours off Aryan Dutt early in the innings.
